    "attribution": {
        "Pikmin 4.txt": "By Hazerou\nIncluded in the text file;\n\n[30 FPS / 60 FPS Gameplay + 30 FPS Cutscene v1]\n[Upscale Quality]\n[Enable / Disable Dynamic Resolution]\n[Dynamic Resolution Target FPS]\n[RRS]\n[Max Quality Override To Highest]\n[Perf Limits on Devices with Battery]\n[Image Sharpening]\n[Forward Shading] & [Deferred Shading]\n[New Film Tone Mapper]\n[Use TAAU]\n[Vignette]\n[Distortion Effects]\n[Foggy Scene]\n[Motion Blur]\n[Film Grain]\n[CHROM AB]\n[Lens Flare]\n[Sky Lighting Quality]\n[Adaptive Exposure]\n[View Distance Scale]\n[DOF]\n[Anisotropic Filtering]\n[Anti-Aliasing (FXAA, TAA & MSAA]\n[Shadow]\n[Shadow Distance]\n[SSAO]\n[Bloom]\n[SSR]\n[SSS]\n[SSS Scale] <= NEW!\n[SSGI] <= NEW!\n[Refraction]\n[Light Function Quality]\n\nNote;\n\nGame is using Double Buffering. If using 60 FPS, use it with [Enable DRS] + [Dynamic Resolution Target 60 FPS].\n\n=====\n[Upscale Quality] Is also known as Graphics Texture Filtering and it's noticeable (more usable) when using lower RRS + AA OFF, + AA Very Low or + AA Low.\n\nType-0: Nearest filtering\n\nType-1: Simple Bilinear\n\nType-2: Directional blur with unsharp mask upsample. (default)\n\nType-3: 5-tap Catmull-Rom bicubic, approximating Lanczos 2.\n\nType-4: 13-tap Lanczos 3.\n\nType-5: 36-tap Gaussian-filtered unsharp mask (very expensive, but good for extreme upsampling)\n\n=====\n\n[RRS] is Render Resolution Scale and it disables Dynamic Resolution Function.\nPlease use;\nHandheld RRS for Handheld Mode.\nDocked RRS for Docked Mode.\nDon't activate them at the same time!\n\n[SSR] Is Screen Space Reflection.\n\n[SSS] Is Subsurface Scattering.\n\n[SSGI] Is Screen Space Global Illumination.\n\nSome GFX Codes has no Function/Effect to the Game.\n"
    }
}